Coconut Lentil Soup with Lemongrass and Ginger

2 c red lentils (or yellow split peas) sorted and rinsed well
1 onion, diced
6-8c vegetable broth (add less for ticker soup)
2 c diced pumpkin or butternut suqash
1 can full fat coconut milk
1 tbsp lemongrass paste
1 tbsp fresh ginger finely grated
1 tbsp fresh garlic
1 tbsp curry powder 
2 kaffir lime leaves, fresh or frozen (or strips of lime zest)
salt to taste
a little sugar
fresh cilantro for garnish
sliced green onions for garnish
sliced green or red thai chiles for garnish

Place lentils, onion, and vegetable broth in a 3-4 quart pot. Bring to a simmer, cover and cook until lentils start to soften, ~15-20min. Add the diced squash, coconut milk, lemongrass, ginger, garlic, and kaffir lime leaves. Season with salt to taste. Bring back to a low simmer and cook until the lentils have completely broken down and squash is tender. Taste and adjust seasonings as desired. Add a pinch of sugar. Serve over rice.
